         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, 22nd August 1889 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ In reply to the enquiry by the Secretary to the Public Service Board ¶ See M to A. Deakin, 5 August 1889,and notes thereto. ¶  ¶ regarding any alteration in the ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">89.08.22</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">N89/10332, unit 458, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS written by Georg Luehmann and signed by M.</p>
               </note>Melbourne, 22nd August 1889</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to the enquiry by the Secretary to the Public Service Board<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to A. Deakin, 5 August 1889,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and notes thereto.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>regarding any alteration in the duties, performed by Mr. French,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Charles French Snr.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have the honor to inform you that, although the services rendered are still in the same direction as formerly, they are of a higher grade and are performed more expeditiously on account of increased experience. In my opinion the increment enjoyed by him of £6 per annum, which moreover will soon come to an end, is disproportinate to the enhanced value of his services.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 26 August 1889,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Wilson forwarded M's letter to the Public Service Board,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>whose secretary minuted<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on 29 August that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>’the Board<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sees<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>no reason for an alteration in the status of the office'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The Secretary of the Board, H. Gomm, returned the file to Wilson,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>directing his attention to their minute. Wilson sent the file to M on 2 September for information,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and he<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>returned it on 5 September 'with acknowledgment of the information'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Govt. Botanist</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">T. R. Wilson Esq</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Under Secretary</p>
         </div>
